name: Skagit County Public Health- Fairgrounds
notes:
Pfizer Dose 1 & 2 Vaccine Clinic for all aged 12+
•	North Entrance to Skagit County Fairgrounds 1410 Virginia Street, Mount Vernon WA
•	Child watching provided
•	Vaccination process will take approximately 1 hour.  Wheel chairs and accessible parking available for people with mobility challenges.
•	All forms available in English and Spanish.  Spanish language interpretation provided.  
•	Dose 2 appointments scheduled 3 weeks following 

We are unable to vaccinate people who have received another vaccine of any type within 14 days OR those that have severe allergic reactions to vaccines or injectable medications.


Clínica de vacunas de primer y Segundo dosis Pfizer años 12+
•	Entrada norte al recinto ferial del condado de Skagit 1410 Virginia Street, Mount Vernon WA
•	Vigilancia de niños proveída
•	El proceso de vacunación durará aproximadamente 1 hora. Sillas de ruedas y estacionamiento accesible para personas con problemas de movilidad.
•	Todos los formularios están disponibles en inglés y español. Interpretación en español será proveída.

No podemos vacunar a personas que hayan recibido otra vacuna de cualquier tipo durante los ultimos 14 días O personas que tengan reacciones alérgicas graves a vacunas o medicamentos inyectables.
Citas reservadas 3 semanas después para la segunda dosis.
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Onestop Medical Clinic - Covid Vaccination Venue
notes:
• Onestop Medical, a Primary Care Clinic is serving the community by administering COVID-19 vaccines as a giving back in the current difficult situation since January 2021. Please DO NOT disrespect our hardworking staff and volunteers. No profanity please.
	
	• Due to the social distancing limitations and limited parking, please plan to arrive NO earlier than 5 Minutes. Please DO NOT park in front of our neighbor’s building; 1316 Central Ave S. The extra public parking is available next door at the Kent Municipal Court (1220 Central Ave S, Kent, WA 98032).
	
	• We ask that for everyone’s safety, please DO NOT visit this vaccination drive without an appointment. Please DO NOT email or call us to inquire, schedule, reschedule, cancel your appointment about COVID-19 Vaccine as we are experiencing extremely high email and call volumes. Please DO NOT book an appointment from the Zocodoc or Onestop Medical's website for COVID-19 Immunization.
	
	• Please schedule your Dose 2 through Prepmod.doh.wa.gov between 21 to 42 (at least 17 days considering grace period) days apart. Please DO NOT laminate the vaccine card. 
 
	• Please remember that you will need to bring your photo ID/Passport, medical insurance card (if insured). If you're receiving your 2nd vaccination, you will be required to bring your vaccination card too.

	• We DO NOT accept any form of payment, donation for COVID-19 vaccine from any patient. Please DO NOT make any payment to the Onestop Medical. If you receive a bill for your COVID vaccine, please contact your insurance company First.
	If you DO NOT have an insurance, no worries and you will still receive your vaccine.
	If you have Insurance a small Admin Fee will be charged to the insurance. The patient DOES NOT PAY for any vaccine related services out-of-pocket  The Admin Fee will be used to help cover a portion of the cost to maintain the staff, PPEs and all medical need.
	
	https://www.doh.wa.gov/Emergencies/COVID19/VaccineInformation/VaccineCost#heading67668
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Walla Walla County HD- COVID Provider
notes:
**THIS CLINIC IS BY APPOINTMENT ONLY FOR 1st DOSE PFIZER VACCINATIONS for all individuals aged 16 years & over. This will be at the Providence Southgate Medical Park main building (the former Walla Walla General Hospital) 1025 South 2nd Ave. Participants are advised to stay to their right as they enter the campus and proceed to the main entrance, instead of going to Urgent Care. COVID vaccine is not available in Urgent Care.
Given the limited supply of COVID-19 vaccine available at this time and Washington's commitment to equitable and fair access, those seeking COVID-19 vaccines at this clinic location you must either live or work, or get your medical care in Washington state.  Masks are required. If you do not have a mask, one will be provided. 
We look forward to seeing you. Thanks for keeping Walla Walla well.

** ESTA CLÍNICA ES CON CITA SOLAMENTE PARA LAS VACUNAS DE LA PRIMERA DOSIS DE PFIZER para personas de 16 años en adelante.** Esto será en el edificio principal de Providence Southgate Medical Park, (antes conocido como el Hospital General de Walla Walla)1025 Sur 2nd ave.  Se recomienda a los participantes que se mantengan a su derecha al ingresar y que se dirijan a la entrada principal, en lugar de ir a Atención de Urgencia.  La Vacuna COVID no está disponible en Atención de Urgencias. 
Dado el suministro limitado de la vacuna COVID-19 disponible en este momento y el compromiso de Washington con el acceso equitativo y justo, aquellos que buscan vacunas para el COVID-19 en esta clínica deben vivir o trabajar, o recibir atención médica en el estado de Washington.  El cubre bocas es requerido. Si no tiene un cubre bocas, se le proporcionará una. Esperamos verlo. Gracias por cuidar a Walla Walla.
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Yakima County Health District COVID Vaccination Site
notes: ***1ST & 2nd DOSE PFIZER VACCINATIONS***!!!!VACUNAS DE PRIMERA Y SECUNDA DOSIS DE PFIZER!!!! The vaccination clinic will take place at Yakima Valley College. Enter the YVC campus at the intersection between S 16th Ave and Arlington St. Continue on Arlington St and turn right onto S 12th Ave. The vaccination site will be at the parking lot next to the baseball field and bookstore. Masks are required. Please wear clothing which allows access to your shoulder. Vaccinations at this site are reserved for people who live and/or work in Washington State. All individuals 16 and over are eligible to get vaccinated. Those under 18 must be accompanied by a parent/guardian or must get parental consent via video/phone call or paper format. La clínica de vacunación se ubicara en Yakima Valley College. Ingrese al campus de YVC en la intersección entre S 16th Ave y Arlington St. Continue en Arlington St y gire a la derecha en S 12th Ave. El sitio de vacunación estará en el estacionamiento junto al campo de beisbol y la librería. Se requieren máscaras. Por favor, use ropa que permita acceso a su brazo. Las vacunas en este sitio están reservadas para las personas que viven o trabajan en el estado de Washington. Todas las personas mayores de 16 años son elegibles para vacunarse. Los menores de 18 años deben estar acompañados por un padre/tutor o deben obtener el consentimiento de los padres por video/llamada telefónica o en papel. ***1ST AND 2nd DOSE PFIZER VACCINATIONS***!!!!VACUNAS DE PRIMERA Y SEGUNDA DOSIS DE PFIZER!!!!
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
